OL,3,CWhy are we seeing more hail even
OL,4,Cthough the weather is warming up?
OL,6,FOver the past week many people were
OL,7,Fshocked as areas across the UK were
OL,8,Fhit with hailstones.
OL,10,FBut while you may think hail is a
OL,11,Fwinter phenomenon ` think again.
OL,13,FNot only can the downpours happen all
OL,14,Fyear round, it is actually more of a
OL,15,Fspring and summer phenomenon.
OL,17,FWhat is hail and how does it form?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779267997
OL,3,CWhy are we seeing more hail even
OL,4,Cthough the weather is warming up?
OL,6,FHailstones are lumps of ice ranging in
OL,7,Fsize from smaller than a pea to the
OL,8,Fsize of a melon - thankfully not in
OL,9,Fthe UK - and are made from layers of
OL,10,Ffrozen water droplets.
OL,12,FThey develop inside storm clouds, when
OL,13,Fstrong updraughts of wind carry water
OL,14,Fdroplets high into very cold parts of
OL,15,Fthe atmosphere, where they freeze.
OL,17,FWhile you might not associate hail
OL,18,Fwith the summer months, this process
OL,19,Fexplains why downpours increase in
OL,20,Fwarmer weather.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
