PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779267997
OL,3,CWhy are we seeing more hail even
OL,4,Cthough the weather is warming up?
OL,6,FWarm air always rises - the warmer the
OL,7,Fair, the faster and higher it will
OL,8,Frise.
OL,10,FEven in the driest parts of the world,
OL,11,Fair contains water vapour and as it
OL,12,Frises, it cools and condenses into
OL,13,Fdroplets which form clouds.
OL,15,FThe rising air is called an updraught.
OL,17,FWhen temperatures are warm enough,
OL,18,Fthis updraught is supercharged and the
OL,19,Fair is lifted higher into the sky.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
