FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779267997
OL,3,CWhy are we seeing more hail even
OL,4,Cthough the weather is warming up?
OL,6,FThere it forms skyscraper style clouds
OL,7,Fwhich are sometimes called thunder
OL,8,Fclouds.
OL,10,FThe water droplets rise high enough to
OL,11,Ffreeze, becoming little pellets of ice.
OL,13,FThey continue to rise, fall and swirl
OL,14,Fwithin the thunderclouds, while
OL,15,Fgathering more layers of water
OL,16,Fdroplets and becoming slightly bigger
OL,17,Fballs of ice. This is hail.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
