PN,31509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779267997
OL,3,CWhy are we seeing more hail even
OL,4,Cthough the weather is warming up?
OL,6,FAt 20cm in diameter, 47.3cm in
OL,7,Fcircumference and weighing nearly a
OL,8,Fkilogram (0.88kg), it was a bit like a
OL,9,Flarge grapefruit, according to the
OL,10,FNational Oceanic and Atmospheric
OL,11,FAdministration and the National
OL,12,FWeather Service.
OL,14,FIt was calculated to have fallen to
OL,15,Fearth at around 100mph!
OL,17,FThis 'super hail' requires extreme
OL,18,Fheat, creating incredibly powerful
OL,19,Fthunderstorms called 'supercells' so,
OL,20,Ffrozen grapefruits falling from the
OL,21,Fsky in the UK remains unlikely.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
